{{Infobox company | name = Mr.Goodliving | logo = | type = Private (subsidiary of [[RealNetworks]]) | foundation = 1999 | founder = | location = [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]] | key_people = | revenue = | num_employees = | industry = [[Video game industry|Video games]] | owner = | homepage = [http://www.mrgoodliving.com/ www.mrgoodliving.com] }} '''Mr.Goodliving''' Ltd. was a [[Finland|Finnish]] [[video game developer]] and a [[video game publisher]] based in [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]]. It was founded in 1999, and acquired by [[RealNetworks]] on 6 May 2005.<ref>{{cite web| title = REALNETWORKS ENTERS MOBILE GAMES MARKET: ACQUIRES EUROPEAN-BASED MR. GOODLIVING LTD | url = http://investor.realnetworks.com/secfiling.cfm?filingID=1299933-05-2342 | publisher = investor.realnetworks.com }}</ref> Mr.Goodliving was focused on games for [[mobile phones]], the [[iPhone]] and other high-end portable devices.
The company was best known for the casual sports game franchise Playman Sports,<ref>{{cite web| title = Playman Sports | url = http://www.playmansports.com | publisher = www.playmansports.com }}</ref> spanning numerous incarnations such as Playman Summer Games, Playman Winter Games and Playman World Soccer. Along with original [[intellectual property]], the company worked with several high-profile licenses such as Trivial Pursuit,<ref>{{cite web| title = Trivial Pursuit: Deluxe Edition Review | url = http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/r/Mobile/Trivial+Pursuit%3A+Deluxe+Edition/review.asp?c=5227 | publisher = www.pocketgamer.co.uk }}</ref> South Park,<ref>{{cite web| title = South Park Mega Millionaire Review | url = http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/r/Mobile/South+Park+Mega+Millionaire/review.asp?c=15597 | publisher = www.pocketgamer.co.uk }}</ref> Scrabble,<ref>{{cite web| title = Scrabble Mobile Review | url = http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/r/Mobile/Scrabble+Mobile/review.asp?c=10656&srch=scrabble | publisher = www.pocketgamer.co.uk }}</ref> and the Vancouver 2010 Olympic Winter Games.<ref>{{cite web| title = Vancouver 2010 Review | url = http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/r/Mobile/Vancouver+2010/review.asp?c=17790 | publisher = www.pocketgamer.co.uk }}</ref>
In addition to its games, Mr.Goodliving developed EMERGE, a proprietary development platform which enables rapid and scalable publishing of games to more than 2000 handsets in 20 languages.{{Citation needed|date=February 2010}}
On February 9, 2011, Real unexpectedly announced to close Mr.Goodliving.<ref>http://dome.fi/pelit/uutiset/real-sulkee-suomalaisen-mr-goodliving-pelikehittajan-potkut-44lle</ref>
